## 🧑‍🔬 About

**Slicer6D** is an academic research project for advanced 3D print slicing and overhang deformation, built with PyQt5 and PyVista.  

- **Overhang detection and deformation**
- **Custom slicing and G-code generation**
- **Interactive 3D visualization**
- **Layer and toolpath analysis**

---

## 🚦 Project Status

> **This is a prototype.**  
> Expect rapid changes, breaking changes, experimental features, and open issues.  
> Contributions and feedback are welcome!

---

## 🏗️ Features

- **3D Model Visualization** (STL)
- **Overhang Analysis** (angle, support distance, ray tracing)
- **Deformation Tools** (reduce supports)
- **Custom Slicing** (layer height, infill, G-code)
- **Layer/Toolpath View** (interactive slider)
- **Cross-platform** (Linux, Windows, macOS)

---

## 🛠️ Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/DavidSeyserGit/Slicer6D.git
cd Slicer6D
pip install -r requirements.txt
python main.py
